<div id="review_3951478010" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3951478010" />
    <a title="Stephanie Griffin" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/514234-stephanie-griffin"><img alt="Stephanie Griffin" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1191879872p2/514234.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3951478010?book_show_action=true">May 02, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stephanie Griffin" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stephanie Griffin" href="/user/show/514234-stephanie-griffin">Stephanie Griffin</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/51853973-eye-of-the-needle">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3951478010" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3182155414732268206">THE EYE OF THE NEEDLE <br/>This thriller takes place in the U.K. during World War II. A German spy is there, gathering military information and sending it back to Germany.<br/>Many people know this author from his popular historical fiction writing, including the Kingsbridge series and the Century Trilogy. EYE OF THE NEEDLE is one of Follett’s earliest and best loved books.<br/>I thought that generally I was over WWII settings in novels, but I already had this book so I gave it a read and I’m so glad I did. Fr</span>
  <span id="freeText3182155414732268206" style="display:none">THE EYE OF THE NEEDLE <br />This thriller takes place in the U.K. during World War II. A German spy is there, gathering military information and sending it back to Germany.<br />Many people know this author from his popular historical fiction writing, including the Kingsbridge series and the Century Trilogy. EYE OF THE NEEDLE is one of Follett’s earliest and best loved books.<br />I thought that generally I was over WWII settings in novels, but I already had this book so I gave it a read and I’m so glad I did. From reading non-fiction about this era, I know that there were many real spies from all countries involved in this war. Follett turns it up a notch and provides plenty of excitement. In the opening scenes there is a startling, most unexpected incident that made me gasp. I was hooked.<br />When U.K. authorities discover that “Die Nadel” is in their midst, the hunt is on to catch him before he passes on intelligence regarding the next maneuver of the Allies. This chase is the main part of the story. You may have to suspend your disbelief just a wee bit but if you’re reading to give yourself a break from our weary world this will definitely do the trick. To top it all off, an unlikely person is the hero at the end.<br />There’s a reason why this book is a classic - it’s a GREAT STORY. I highly recommend it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3182155414732268206" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


