<div id="review_458348627" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/458348627" />
    <a title="Kaustubh Dudhane" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14694521-kaustubh-dudhane"><img alt="Kaustubh Dudhane" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1617525261p2/14694521.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/458348627?book_show_action=true">Nov 18, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kaustubh Dudhane" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kaustubh Dudhane" href="/user/show/14694521-kaustubh-dudhane">Kaustubh Dudhane</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer458348627" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17851011214158824619">Read sometime in 2014.<br/><br/><b>
  <i>“War was grueling and oppressive and frustrating and uncomfortable, but one had friends. If peace brought back loneliness, Godliman thought he would not be able to live with it.”</i>
</b><br/><br/>This was my first experience with Ken Follett. And dear o dear! What a engrossing experience it was! I still remember how glued I was to the book. The plot, the tension and the intensity of the attraction between the two main characters were absolutely brilliantly written. The fun part was that </span>
  <span id="freeText17851011214158824619" style="display:none">Read sometime in 2014.<br><br><b>
  <i>“War was grueling and oppressive and frustrating and uncomfortable, but one had friends. If peace brought back loneliness, Godliman thought he would not be able to live with it.”</i>
</b><br><br>This was my first experience with Ken Follett. And dear o dear! What a engrossing experience it was! I still remember how glued I was to the book. The plot, the tension and the intensity of the attraction between the two main characters were absolutely brilliantly written. The fun part was that I had never heard of Ken Follett and never checked Goodreads for the review before buying this breakthrough novel from a used-bookstore. <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1608220956ra/30545751.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Moreover, I had never read a book with an anti-hero before this one which was spiced up with feelings of nationalism and intense romance. It was too much for my little mind and I was overwhelmed at that time!<br></span>
  <a data-text-id="17851011214158824619" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
